<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - "ENGINE WARN" WARNING LIGHT,
        CIRCUIT AND CLUSTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>"ENGINE WARN" WARNING LIGHT, CIRCUIT AND CLUSTER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_9.xml" xrefid="x0824515">"Engine Warn" Warning Light
                    <xref refid="x0824515"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for an operation description of the"Engine Warn" light.
            </para>
            <para>With the key ON and engine OFF the light should come ON for a bulb test during the
                Speedometer/Tachometer self-diagnostic test.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Light, Circuit and Cluster</title>
            <table id="t0824526">
                <title>Testing Light, Circuit and Cluster</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove bulb and test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Bulb connectors.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Re-install bulb and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace bulb.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove connector (72) from gauge cluster and disconnect connector
                                    (263)/(341)/(955)*. At connector (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AT.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 97AT, to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 97AT, connector (262), or circuit 97AT, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (263)/(341)/(955)* use a test lead to jumper circuit 97AT to ground.
                                    At (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AT.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 97AT to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Reconnect (263)/(341). Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AT, connector (262), or circuit 97AT,
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>With a good bulb installed, measure resistance between cluster (72) cavity 6 and
                                    cavity 13
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 6 to cavity 13.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open circuit in cluster. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Turn key on. Measure voltage at connector (72) cavity 6 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(72), cavity 6 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect (72), cluster and circuit test good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28A/13D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">* Connector (263) is Cummins M11 and N14 ECM connector.</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">* Connector (955) is Cummins M11 and N14 ECM connector.</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">* Connector (341) is Detroit Diesel Series 60 ECM connector.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
